|CK0The Priests of Set do not actively seek to destroy good, but they are
|CK0neutral at best. Most priests are evil, seeking power and the
|CK0destruction of anything that would prevent them from obtaining that
|CK0power.
|CK0
|CK0Set only lends his power to his followers that follow this evil path.
|CK0Additionally, a priest may find that some or most of their beneficial
|CK0prayers will only apply to other evil aligned players.
|CK0
|CK0At guild level 6, 'dispensation' petitions Set for a five-minute
|CK0exception to the priest's own alignment restriction. It does not bypass
|CK0target alignment or any other rule. During the exception, all direct and
|CK0reserved HP and SP prayer costs, and all prayer cooldowns, are 25 percent
|CK0higher. Dispensation itself has no HP or SP cost and has a ten-minute
|CK0support cooldown.
